Muduo is a multithreaded C++ network library based on the reactor pattern.

http://github.com/chenshuo/muduo

Copyright (c) 2010, Shuo Chen.  All rights reserved.

Use of this source code is governed by a BSD-style license that can be found in
the License file.

This fork is maintained as a Linux-only CMake project.

Requirements
============

Required:

  * Linux kernel version >= 2.6.28
  * CMake >= 3.16
  * GCC or Clang with C++20 support
  * Boost headers
  * pthread

Recommended:

  * Ninja
  * Protobuf and protoc, tested with Protobuf 6.33.6
  * zlib, required by protobuf codec/protorpc targets
  * c-ares, required by cdns and protobuf resolver examples
  * libcurl, required by curl examples

Install packages on Debian/Ubuntu:

  sudo apt install g++ cmake ninja-build libboost-dev
  sudo apt install protobuf-compiler libprotobuf-dev zlib1g-dev
  sudo apt install libc-ares-dev libcurl4-openssl-dev

Build With build.sh
===================

The simplest build entry is:

  ./build.sh -j 4

`build.sh` configures the project with modern CMake and then builds it:

  cmake -S <source> -B <build-dir> -G Ninja ...
  cmake --build <build-dir> -- <arguments>

Default values:

  * BUILD_TYPE=Release
  * BUILD_DIR=out/build/linux-${BUILD_TYPE}
  * INSTALL_DIR=out/install/linux-${BUILD_TYPE}
  * GENERATOR=Ninja
  * BUILD_EXAMPLES=ON
  * ENABLE_PROTOBUF=ON

Common examples:

  # Release build, all default targets
  ./build.sh -j 4

  # Debug build
  BUILD_TYPE=Debug ./build.sh -j 4

  # Build one target
  ./build.sh muduo_protobuf_codec -j 4

  # Build protobuf RPC examples
  ./build.sh protobuf_rpc_all -j 4

  # Configure and build without examples/tests
  BUILD_EXAMPLES=OFF ./build.sh -j 4

  # Disable protobuf support
  ENABLE_PROTOBUF=OFF ./build.sh -j 4

  # Use a custom build directory
  BUILD_DIR=out/build/local-debug BUILD_TYPE=Debug ./build.sh -j 4

`build.sh` also links `compile_commands.json` into the source root for IDEs and
language servers.

Build With CMake
================

Manual configure and build:

  cmake -S . -B out/build/linux-release -G Ninja \
    -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release \
    -DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=out/install/linux-release \
    -DCMAKE_EXPORT_COMPILE_COMMANDS=ON \
    -DMUDUO_BUILD_EXAMPLES=ON \
    -DMUDUO_ENABLE_PROTOBUF=ON

  cmake --build out/build/linux-release -j 4

Install:

  cmake --install out/build/linux-release

Run tests:

  CTEST_OUTPUT_ON_FAILURE=TRUE cmake --build out/build/linux-release --target test

Useful targets:

  * muduo_base
  * muduo_net
  * muduo_http
  * muduo_inspect
  * muduo_protobuf_codec
  * muduo_protorpc
  * protobuf_codec_all
  * protobuf_rpc_all

CMake options:

  * MUDUO_BUILD_EXAMPLES: build examples and tests. Default is ON for a top-level
    build and OFF when muduo is included by another project.
  * MUDUO_ENABLE_PROTOBUF: build protobuf-based libraries/examples when protobuf,
    protoc, and zlib are available. Default is ON.

Build With CMake Presets
========================

Linux presets are provided for IDEs and command-line use:

  * linux-debug-static
  * linux-release-static
  * linux-debug-shared
  * linux-release-shared

Examples:

  cmake --preset linux-debug-shared
  cmake --build out/build/linux-debug-shared -j 4

  cmake --preset linux-release-shared
  cmake --build out/build/linux-release-shared --target protobuf_rpc_all -j 4

Optional Dependencies
=====================

Optional libraries are detected at configure time. If a dependency is missing,
the related examples are skipped instead of breaking the whole build.

Notable optional dependencies:

  * c-ares: enables `muduo_cdns`, `cdns`, and protobuf resolver examples.
  * Protobuf + protoc + zlib: enables protobuf codec/protorpc libraries and
    protobuf examples.
  * libcurl: enables curl examples.
  * gperftools/tcmalloc, hiredis, gd, thrift, microhttpd: enable their related
    examples or optional link paths when available.

If an optional dependency is installed after a failed configure, rerun CMake so
the cache is refreshed:

  cmake -S . -B out/build/linux-release -G Ninja

Notes
=====

The project is intentionally Linux-only. Configuring it on non-Linux systems
will fail at the top-level CMake project.

See https://github.com/chenshuo/muduo-tutorial for how to use muduo in your
project.

